timeline.message:
Exposes CorrelationField and ExtraField Apis

This completes the most common requests around correlation fields by
generalizing code in support for correlation fields, both synchronizing
to logging context and also propagation (extra fields).

Notably, this allows you to not only define constants for the fields you
want, but also decide if they are permissible for correlation.

Ex.

```java
 // configure the field, permitting it to be used in correlation contexts
 static final ExtraField BUSINESS_PROCESS = ExtraField.newBuilder("bp").withCorrelation().build();

 // Allow logging patterns like %X{traceId} %X{bp}
 loggingContext = new Log4J2Context();

 decorator = CorrelationFieldScopeDecorator.newBuilder(loggingContext)
                                           .addField(BUSINESS_PROCESS).build();

 tracingBuilder.propagationFactory(ExtraFieldPropagation.newFactoryBuilder(B3Propagation.FACTORY)
                                                        .flushValuesToContext(loggingContext)
                                                        .addField(BUSINESS_PROCESS)
                                                        .build())
               .currentTraceContext(ThreadLocalCurrentTraceContext.newBuilder()
                                                                  .addScopeDecorator(decorator)
                                                                  .build())

 // Assume runtime code looks like this
 @SendTo(SourceChannels.OUTPUT)
 public void timerMessageSource() {
   BUSINESS_PROCESS.setValue("accounting");
   // The logging expression %{bp} will show "accounting" in businessCode()
   businessCode();
 }
```

