Just an example of what it might look like to pass current value in when closing a scope if it seems useful. replace would check to make sure the current value is currentValue since if it isn't, the scope was closed in the wrong order - happens in reactive apps sometimes 😢 But admittedly having a check like this only for correlation scopes and not our more important ones is probably not so helpful either.

